---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>

<Fragment slot="head-scripts">
  {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}
</Fragment>

<CommercialHero
  eyebrow="Hoshizaki HG-100 · CMA Glass Mizer · Champion CG-2 · Lamb · Moyer Diebel"
  title="Commercial Glass Washer Repair Los Angeles"
  subtitle="Bar glass washers across LA, OC, Ventura, Riverside. $120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. Same-day dispatch. Friday and Saturday bar emergency coverage."
  heroImageTitle="Bar Glass Washer Repair"
  showBranches={true}
/>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · What we service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Bar glass washers, lower temp, faster cycles, etched-glass safe.</h2>

    <p>Glass washers are bar-specific commercial dishwashers, designed differently from undercounter dishwashers. Lower wash temp (130 to 140°F vs 150 to 160°F on dishwashers) preserves etched, hand-blown, and gold-rim glassware that high-temp machines would etch or strip. Faster cycle times (60 to 90 seconds) keep up with bar service throughput. Spinning wash arms (rotational jet thrust) instead of fixed-spray manifolds.</p>

    <p>Three platforms dominate the LA bar segment: <strong>Hoshizaki HG-100</strong> (Hoshizaki commercial line, Japanese-engineered), <strong>CMA Glass Mizer</strong> (Cleveland-based commercial dishwasher specialist), <strong>Champion CG-2</strong> (Ali Group, sister brand to Scotsman ice and Beverage-Air). Plus Lamb LM and Moyer Diebel on legacy installs.</p>

    <p>BHGS #A49573. EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. $120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair, no emergency surcharge.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">02 · Typical glass washer failures</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Six failure modes account for most glass washer calls.</h2>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Wash arm jets clogged with bar residue.</strong> Sugar syrup, citrus pulp, beer foam protein, espresso oils, all clog small-diameter glass washer jets faster than dishwasher jets. Spinning relies on jet thrust, clogged jets means no rotation. Cleaning service $200 to $340.</li>
      <li><strong>Detergent and rinse aid dispensers.</strong> Glass washers run high-frequency dispense cycles. Solenoid coils corrode from chemical exposure faster than dishwasher solenoids. Replacement $260 to $400.</li>
      <li><strong>Drain pump (frequent cycling).</strong> Bar service produces 200+ cycles per shift on busy nights, drain pump impeller wear at year 4 to 6 typical. $300 to $480.</li>
      <li><strong>Door switch (frequent open/close at bar).</strong> Bartender opens and closes glass washer constantly during service. Switch wears at year 3 to 5. $200 to $340.</li>
      <li><strong>Water inlet valve.</strong> Hard SoCal water plus high-frequency cycling stresses inlet valve diaphragm. Failure at year 4 to 6. $280 to $440.</li>
      <li><strong>Wash arm bearing seizure.</strong> Sustained jet imbalance from clogged jets eventually seizes the arm bearing. Replacement $360 to $540 plus arm rebalancing.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">03 · Recent jobs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Real repair stories from the last few weeks.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Composite examples; model numbers, ages, and prices are accurate to typical scope.</p>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>West Hollywood · Hoshizaki HG-100 craft cocktail bar, 5 years old</h3>
      <p>Wash arms barely spinning, glassware spotting. Diagnosed: jets clogged with citrus pulp and sugar syrup residue, detergent dispenser feed rate dropping. Deep cleaned wash arms, descaled inlet manifold, replaced detergent dispenser solenoid. Total: $120 plus $260 part plus 1.5 hours = $440.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Beverly Hills · CMA Glass Mizer hotel bar, 8 years old</h3>
      <p>Drain pump running but slow, water sitting in tank. Replaced drain pump (impeller heavily worn from year 8 of bar service). Tested 5 cycles. Total: $120 plus $300 part plus 1 hour = $480.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Pasadena · Champion CG-2 restaurant bar, 6 years old</h3>
      <p>Cycle starting thin, water inlet running long. Diagnosed: water inlet valve diaphragm degraded plus detergent dispenser feed inconsistent. Replaced both. Total: $120 plus $360 parts plus 1.5 hours = $560.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Long Beach · Hoshizaki HG-100 brewpub, 4 years old</h3>
      <p>Door switch intermittent, bartender working around it. Replaced door switch, tested 20 open/close cycles. Total: $120 plus $220 part plus 45 minutes = $380.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story">
      <h3>Burbank · CMA Glass Mizer high-volume sports bar, 7 years old</h3>
      <p>Wash arm bearing seized after months of clogged-jet operation. Replaced wash arm bearing, deep cleaned all jets, calibrated detergent feed. Total: $120 plus $440 parts plus 1.5 hours = $640.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">04 · Honest scope</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we do for glass washers, and what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong> Hoshizaki HG-100, CMA Glass Mizer, Champion CG-2, Lamb LM, Moyer Diebel. Spinning wash arm rebuild and rebalancing, jet cleaning, detergent and rinse aid dispenser solenoids, drain pumps, door switches, water inlet valves, control boards.</p>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong> new glass washer installation under custom bar millwork (cabinetmaker / fabricator trade); glassware washing chemistry consulting (chemical supply rep trade, Ecolab and Auto-Chlor handle that); residential dishwasher service (different scope and tier).</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
